//Alternatively, you can use the Arrays.asList() method to create a list
directly from an array of elements,like this:

List<Integer> my_list = Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4, 5);


                                 OR
                                 
                                 
//In Java, you can define a list using curly braces and
separating the elements with commas, like this:


List<Integer> my_list = new ArrayList<Integer>() {{
    add(1);
    add(2);
    add(3);
    add(4);
    add(5);
}};
